nt exploring and found the wreck of the largest three masted ship ever built in Nova Scotia!!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/yX8SCQD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/j2sbAut.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>After some heavy rains this summer, we heard about an old ship that was now visible on the beach</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9YPLWbW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We took a drive out to see for ourselves</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WCYrMWH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Apparently The Hamburg (and the two other ships beside it in the sand) were abandoned here in the early 1920s</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/w8IoggT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>They’d been completely buried for so long, the community forgot they were there, and when the beach eroded, the originally thought it was an old wharf</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Z94bu4P.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That’s a pretty curvy wharf though!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nmO7BN4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here’s where a stream has cut between the main part of the ship, and the prow</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UM1Mrge.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some of the ship’s internal structure was visible as well</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/t7lmkK2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here’s the outline of 2 more, side by side under the shoreline</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ld3kWwc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>To give a sense of size, here’s a pic from 1925 - look at the person on the beach on the bottom right of the boat!! You can see one of the other ships beside it.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8yiewcL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It was quite the ship in its day. The biggest of its kind ever built in Nova Scotia!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/yX8SCQD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[drawnbyjohn]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Golden immediately becomes best friends with cat</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/LHaUutr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/p2rV3Qq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Let’s be honest, goldens become best friends with everything immediately</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/LHaUutr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tampacl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>English Lesson</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/m8vB0eh</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/R20b4UW.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/m8vB0eh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SweepTheLeg31]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fish and fries on sale</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YnoEiAD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HC8kwD1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YnoEiAD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Fulustreka]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Steve is not the employee of the week anymore</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Ta20s1f</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vgCvhDc.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3f8Lyv5.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;